transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I assist you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I have a pending order, but then I got an email saying that I needed to record a video.

Speaker 1: So I recorded a video and sent it, but then it said something like—

Speaker 2: Something about—

Speaker 1: Going offline or something. I don't know if it took it or not.

Speaker 2: In the event that it doesn't take it, and in the event that—

Speaker 1: The—

Speaker 2: Medical professional, for whatever reason, is not—

Speaker 1: What do you call it?

Speaker 2: Grants the prescription. I won't be charged, correct?

Speaker 1: No, you won't. So if they won't approve the order, you're going to get a refund for whatever you paid.

Speaker 2: Great, okay.

Speaker 1: Let me take a look to see if we received that video, though.

Speaker 2: If not, you can send it to us by text message, which is a lot easier than going through that link.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: What's your name?

Speaker 1: Sherwin, S-H-E-R-W-Y-N, last name Simon, S-I-M-O-N. And your zip code?

Speaker 2: Two five five five zero. That's three fives and a zero. Thank you.

Speaker 1: And then—

Speaker 2: Yeah, we received your video. We received it, so that's good.

Speaker 1: I'm just—let me quickly just make sure that there's audio to it. Give me one moment.

Speaker 2: Okay, the other thing I wanted to ask you—

Speaker 1: I got confused on checkout because it said something like if you wanted additional something—

Speaker 2: And then I said I declined it, then it said if you want additional something—

Speaker 1: I'm—I must have hit it, yes, or whatever. So, and they're not being 99 went to—

Speaker 2: $145.

Speaker 1: With additional, I get, I guess, 25 tabs, but can you confirm the order? I couldn't understand exactly what happened there.

Speaker 2: Yeah, sure.

Speaker 1: So it looks like your initial order was for 25 pills.

Speaker 2: And then it gives you an option to add an additional 12 pills for a discounted price.

Speaker 1: So that was what was added to your order.

Speaker 2: So 12 pills. So that's for additional—how much? How many dollars?

Speaker 1: I'm sorry, for 12 pills you paid an additional twenty-nine dollars and seventy cents.

Speaker 2: So that's a bitch. So that's a total of how many pills?

Speaker 1: 37.

Speaker 2: Okay, at a hundred milligrams. And I think I spoke to one of your colleagues. She said—

Speaker 1: You can divide them up, you can split them up or break in half or whatever, something like that.

Speaker 2: She said it would—it's a better buy.

Speaker 1: But then I—one more question. If I would have rejected that, was there another one? Was there like—

Speaker 2: Another window that would have said—

Speaker 1: Twelve more pills for like twelve dollars or something like better, but was that the last window? That's a lot.

Speaker 2: The one you selected is the last window, so you have an option of adding an additional 25 pills or half of that.

Speaker 1: Which is the 12 pills? Okay, which I did. Okay, very well. All right?

Speaker 2: Well, I'll just wait for the approval and they'll verify whether it's approved or not, and then we go from there, correct?

Speaker 1: Yes, right, exactly.

Speaker 2: Thank you so much for your time. I appreciate your—

Speaker 1: Welcome, of course.

Speaker 2: Enjoy the rest of your day.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Yep, you too.
